<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="ai">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-robot"></i> AI Assistant</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">The AI button lets you automatically fix specific lines of code using the AI service.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Fix a Line</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>Click the <strong>AI</strong> button in the editor toolbar</li>
<li>Enter the line number you want fixed</li>
<li>Click <strong>Fix Line</strong> &mdash; the AI will rewrite that line</li>
<li>Lines are counted HTML first, then CSS, then JS</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="backups">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Backup System</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">Backups save your current tab content to your <strong>browser LocalStorage</strong>. They are fast and private, but have important limitations.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-warning">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Important Limitations</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> Backups are stored <strong>only in this browser</strong> on this device</li>
<li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> Clearing browser data <strong>deletes all backups permanently</strong></li>
<li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> Backups do <strong>not sync</strong> across devices or browsers</li>
<li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> They are <strong>not saved to the server</strong></li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-list"></i> How to Use</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>Click <strong>Backups</strong> in the editor bar, then <strong>Create Backup</strong></li>
<li>To restore, open Backups and click <strong>Load Backups</strong></li>
<li>Each backup is identified by a unique timestamp ID</li>
<li>You can delete individual backups or select all and delete in bulk</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="tabs">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Tab System</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">Tabs let you work on multiple separate projects in the same editor session.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i> Tab Actions</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>Add Tab</strong> &mdash; creates a new empty workspace</li>
<li><strong>Fork Tab</strong> &mdash; duplicates the current tab with a new name</li>
<li><strong>Save Tab</strong> &mdash; saves the tab to LocalStorage so it reappears on reload</li>
<li><strong>Duplicate Tab</strong> &mdash; creates an identical copy</li>
<li><strong>Close All Tabs</strong> &mdash; removes all unsaved tabs</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-info">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-save"></i> Saved Tabs</div>
<p>Saved tabs are marked with a <strong>&#x1F4BE;</strong> icon and will automatically reload when you visit the page. Deleting a saved tab removes it permanently from LocalStorage.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="share">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-share-alt"></i> Sharing</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">Share your code with a temporary link that expires automatically.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-link"></i> How Sharing Works</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>Click <strong>Share</strong> and choose an expiry time (1&ndash;10 minutes)</li>
<li>A unique short URL is generated and copied to your clipboard</li>
<li>Anyone with the link can view the shared tab in the editor</li>
<li>The link expires automatically at the chosen time &mdash; expired shares show a 404 page</li>
<li>Share data is encrypted in the redirect URL using AES-256-GCM so it cannot be tampered with in transit</li>
<li><strong>Maximum share payload:</strong> 128 KB per tab (HTML + CSS + JS combined)</li>
<li>The server keeps up to <strong>100,000 active share records</strong> before the oldest are pruned</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-warning">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Share Safety Reminder</div>
<p>Do <strong>not</strong> share code containing passwords, API keys, or confidential information.</p>
</div>
<li>Click <strong>Read.me</strong> then choose <strong>Public</strong> (admin only) or <strong>Personal</strong></li>
<li>Public links expire in <strong>1 to 10 minutes</strong> and open as read-only tabs for recipients</li>
<li>Personal read-me tabs are stored locally in your browser</li>
<li>Shared code is stored in the server database until it expires</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
