<div class="mlp-docs-section" data-section="tos-10">
<div class="mlp-docs-section-heading"><i class="fas fa-bolt" style="color:#f0c040;"></i> Term 10 — Platform Capacity &amp; Fair Use</div>
<p class="mlp-docs-lead">ptero.us.ci v5.9.0 has been upgraded with a high-performance infrastructure layer designed to serve up to <strong>100,000 concurrent users</strong>. These improvements come with updated fair-use obligations for all users.</p>
<div class="mlp-docs-card" style="border-color:rgba(240,192,64,0.4);background:rgba(240,192,64,0.05);">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-server"></i> What Changed in v5.9.0</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li><strong>In-Memory Rate Limiting:</strong> All request rate limits are now enforced via a high-speed in-memory cache (Redis/APCu). Circumventing this system via automation, proxies, or VPN rotation is a violation of these Terms</li>
<li><strong>Global Daily AI Cap:</strong> The platform enforces a shared limit of <strong>10,000 AI requests per day</strong> across all users. This is a shared resource &mdash; abuse by any single user degrades the experience for everyone</li>
<li><strong>Chunked Cleanup System:</strong> Database maintenance now runs in controlled batches. Deliberately triggering mass data creation to stress the cleanup system is prohibited</li>
<li><strong>Share Table Capacity:</strong> The platform stores up to <strong>100,000 share records</strong>. Automated share creation to exhaust this capacity is a violation</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card mlp-docs-card-warning">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-ban"></i> Fair Use Obligations</div>
<ul class="mlp-docs-list">
<li>You must not use scripts, bots, or automation to send AI requests in excess of the natural 60-second cooldown</li>
<li>You must not rotate IPs, use VPNs, or use proxies to bypass per-IP rate limits</li>
<li>You must not attempt to flood the AI queue or cache to degrade service for other users</li>
<li>You must not attempt to reverse-engineer or manipulate the rate-limit or circuit-breaker mechanisms</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="mlp-docs-card">
<div class="mlp-docs-card-title"><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Enforcement</div>
<p>Violations result in immediate permanent ban. Severe cases may be referred to relevant authorities.</p>
</div>
</div>
